                     <p> SADYNGTON. Condition of a grant from <persName>sir <forename>William</forename> de  <surname>Botereaux</surname>, kt.</persName>, 
               to <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Cook</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108148">Leicester</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               of an animal rent charge of Â£6 upon his lands and tenements in
               <placeName key="place_1083428">Hardwick, co. Bucks</placeName>, during the life of
               <persName nymRef="Botereaux">
                           <forename>Elizabeth</forename>, wife</persName> of the
               said sir William, namely that if the said Elizabeth does not recover her dower out
               of the manor of <placeName type="manor" key="place_1083650">Sadyngton</placeName>, held by
               the said John, then the said grant of annuity shall become void. 
               Dated the Friday on the feast of the translation of St. Thomas the martyr, 
               <origDate notBefore="1373-01-25" notAfter="1374-01-24">47 Ed. III</origDate>.
                </p>
